<br>
If you look at soloing, it's usually kill something that have at least that much downtime. Duoing (especially some kind of melee + healer) changes things entirely. With single pulls, there is very little downtime. Having said that though, adds are a pain. First of all you need to smack both mobs around a bit if you want the healer to be able to med and/or heal without drawing aggro. With singles it is much easier to be able to slow, heal, and med without getting aggro.<br>
<br>
Also, look at it this way: Let's say you pull two mobs and just kill the first one as fast as possible before going to the second one. By the time you've killed the first one, you've taken a full fight's worth of damage from two mobs. Then you go on to the second one, and you've taken another full fight's worth of damage. So in the length of time it takes to do two fights, you've taken an extra fight's worth of damage. Seems better to just pull them one at a time to me.<br>
<br>
Adds tend to be a real sap on my shaman's mana. I can handle adds just fine yes, but it's usually much more efficient to do them one at a time.<br>
<br>
