<br>
Slow + PE + Malo if the crap really doesn't wanna stay rooted, and it's out of your hair as long as you need it to be.<br>
<br>
Either that, or you can just have the shammy tank one like I do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Medding is for pansies, or people without cann 5 :P<br>
<br>
Seriously, in a war/shaman duo, it's easier to just turn on autoattack on the warrior and really play the shaman, rather than consider the shaman the 2nd priority.<br>
<br>
Usually if I pull 2 and don't feel like rooting, i'll just slow one, usually pulling it on to my shammy, slow the one on my warrior, epic it, epic the one on the shammy, and then beat the living tar out of the one aggro on the shaman while the warrior has autoattack on.  Shamans have some pretty massive DPS.  Epic + bane + Pox + JBB makes for pretty much anything dead in about 60 seconds.  Only catch is you gotta have a SHAMAN, not a druid for this to be effective.  A lot of people 2 box their healers with wisdom/manapool in mind.  Shamans are all about hp/ac, just like warriors.  1000ac, 2800hp and your shaman can tank damned near anything you're xp'ing off.  Cann 5 + torpor after every fight, and you're back in the game, no matter how much mana you spent.<br>
<br>
Clerics are cool if your bot is only gonna be level 40, druids are alright for powerleveling, but if you plan on being an AA machine, absolutely nothing beats a shaman.  Cann 5, spell casting reinforcement, quickbuff, epic, jbb, fungi, and you've got a character that never, ever runs out of mana, can heal 1800hp for 200 mana, and can come back from rezzed to fully buffed and full hp/mana in 4.5 minutes flat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaminy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taminy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/2/02 10:38:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1219.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Making a healer to 2 box with</span><hr size=1> I guess I'm a pansy, I don't have cann5 yet - less than 3 aa points to go though and I can't wait.<br>
